  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        The definition of a fulminant acute myocarditis was the presence of a rapid onset of
        aggressive life-threatening disease accompanied by cardiogenic shock with multiple organ
        dysfunction syndrome, acute severe heart failure, fatal arrhythmias, high-degree
        atrioventricular blockade, or sudden cardiac death following a flu-like illness.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Clinical diagnosis of acute fulminant myocarditis

        Exclusion Criteria:

        chronic renal dysfunction refuse medical treatments
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
